		"description": "<p>You have moved beyond the role of support in the field to keeping records of the exploits of your unit or companions. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Your Strength, Dexterity, or Charisma score increases by 1, to a maximum of 20.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with the History skill or an expertise die if you are already proficient. You also learn two History skill specialties of your choice. They do not count against your skill specialties known.</li>\n<li>Half your fighter levels count as bard levels for the purpose of the Bardic Legend feature.</li>\n<li>Whenever you deal thunder damage to a creature by any means, it must make a Constitution save against your spell save DC or be deafened and rattled until the end of its next turn.</li>\n</ul>",
